cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category, as the paper focuses on analyzing the energy consumption of cryptographic primitives in Android devices.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely, as the paper aims to help Android application developers choose the most energy efficient cryptographic algorithms.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category, as the paper uses an energy profiling tool to measure the power consumption of cryptographic primitives.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is a possible category, as energy efficiency is an important consideration in distributed and parallel computing systems.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a less likely category, but still possible, as the paper discusses the selection of cryptographic algorithms in software development.
